=E2=80=9CIt is all going to get so much dumber,=E2=80=9D I  wrote yesterday=
, about Elon Musk=E2=80=99s efforts to get out of his deal to buy Twitter I=
nc. by complaining about bots. Seventy-three minutes later, Texas Attorney =
General Ken Paxton tweeted this:Today I=E2=80=99m investigating Twitter for=
 potentially misleading Texans on the number of its =E2=80=9Cbot=E2=80=9D u=
sers. I have a duty to protect Texans if Twitter is misrepresenting how man=
y accounts are fake to drive up their revenue.The press release is =E2=80=
=A6=C2=A0so dumb?=C2=A0Twitter has received intense scrutiny in recent week=
s over claiming in its financial regulatory filings that fewer than 5% of a=
ll users are bots, when they may in fact comprise as much as 20% or more. T=
he difference could dramatically affect the cost to Texas consumers and bus=
inesses who transact with Twitter. =C2=A0To address this concern, Attorney =
General Paxton issued a Civil Investigative Demand (CID) to investigate whe=
ther Twitter=E2=80=99s reporting on real versus fake users is =E2=80=9Cfals=
e, misleading, or deceptive=E2=80=9D under the Texas Deceptive Trade Practi=
ces Act. The CID requires Twitter to turn over documents related to how it =
calculates and manages its user data and how these numbers relate to Twitte=
r=E2=80=99s advertising businesses. Twitter has until June 27 to respond to=
 Attorney General Paxton=E2=80=99s Demand. =C2=A0To be clear, Twitter has c=
laimed that bots are fewer than 5% of =E2=80=9Cmonetizable daily active use=
rs=E2=80=9D (not =E2=80=9Call users=E2=80=9D) for=C2=A0eight years, and the=
 =E2=80=9Cintense scrutiny in recent weeks=E2=80=9D consists entirely of El=
on Musk claiming, with no evidence, that there are a lot of bots because he=
 regrets agreeing to buy Twitter for $54.20 per share just before a market =
crash. This is a regulatory investigation entirely for the purposes of trol=
ling: Paxton is harassing Twitter because (1) Musk moved to Texas, (2) Musk=
 announced, like two weeks ago, that he=E2=80=99s a Republican, (3) Musk ha=
s a passionate fan base on Twitter, and (4) Musk is trying to rile up that =
fan base against Twitter by complaining about bots. So Paxton is happy to h=
itch himself to that: If he harasses Twitter on Musk=E2=80=99s behalf, he w=
ill endear himself to Musk=E2=80=99s fans online, which seems valuable for =
an elected official though not, of course, for his constituents, or for the=
 rule of law.=C2=A0The fact that this is all completely fake is beside the =
point, as is the fact that Paxton himself is currently under indictment for=
 felony securities fraud. This all seems bad! I don=E2=80=99t know what to =
tell you! This is not how one wants one=E2=80=99s democracy to be going!=C2=
=A0Elsewhere: =E2=80=9CMusk=E2=80=99s =E2=80=98Buyer=E2=80=99s Remorse=E2=
=80=99 Won=E2=80=99t Get Him Out of Twitter Deal,=E2=80=9D  says Bloomberg =
News.=C2=A0Man, who knows?=C2=A0
