fer a bundle of services. A VC firm does, or tries to do, at least four thi=
ngs:</p><ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: =
16px 0;">=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">It raises money.</li>=09<li s=
tyle=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">It picks good companies to invest the money in=
.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">It convinces the companies to <e=
m>take=C2=A0</em>the money: In a world flush with money, VCs often compete =
to give companies money, rather than the reverse.</li>=09<li style=3D"margi=
n-bottom: 5px;">It helps the companies become better, giving them advice on=
 business and finance and governance and so forth.</li></ol><p style=3D"mar=
gin: 16px 0;">Here is a Wall Street Journal <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bl=
oombergbusiness.com/click/27976693.262609/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cud3NqLmNvbS9hcnRpY=
