undraising), and an alternative asset manager with $100 billion of assets c=
an charge at least a billion dollars a year=C2=A0for doing that job. Outsou=
rcing it to Bain for $100 million seems like a bargain. On the other hand, =
Tiger Global=E2=80=99s =E2=80=9Chedge fund, which managed $23 billion at th=
e end of 2021, was down 52% this year,=E2=80=9D and Tiger=E2=80=99s princip=
als had a lot of their own money in the fund. Meanwhile=C2=A0Bain gets to k=
