 the difference. If at maturity a Bitcoin is worth $32,000, you pay me $2,0=
00; if it=E2=80=99s worth $27,000, I pay you $3,000.</p><p style=3D"margin:=
 16px 0;">To do this sort of cash settlement, you need a reliable reference=
 price for Bitcoin: We need to cash settle against some official price of B=
itcoin. Particularly back when Bitcoin futures were just getting started, U=
S regulators worried that the markets for Bitcoin were too opaque and manip=
ulated to generate a reliable official price; the SEC still won=E2=80=99t a=
pprove <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/27976693.26=
2609/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuY25iYy5jb20vMjAyMi8wNS8wMy9zZWMtbGF5cy1vdXQtcGF0aC10by=
1jb3ZldGVkLXNwb3QtYml0Y29pbi1ldGYtYnV0Lmh0bWw/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBc95b=
a438" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" styl=
e=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width:=
 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-=
color: #ccc;">spot Bitcoin exchange-traded funds</a> because of worries lik=
e that. But the CFTC eventually did approve some cash-settled Bitcoin futur=
es products because it got comfortable that the underlying markets for Bitc=
oin were good enough.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Last Friday the CFTC =
<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/27976693.262609/aH=
R0cHM6Ly93d3cuY2Z0Yy5nb3YvUHJlc3NSb29tL1ByZXNzUmVsZWFzZXMvODU0MC0yMg/607f07=
ceef4b8524a319a23cBe488c34c" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope"=
 target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !importan=
t; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-st=
yle: solid; background-color: #ccc;">sued Gemini Trust Co.</a> for allegedl=
y lying about how good those markets were, as part of its efforts to get a =
Bitcoin futures contract approved in 2017:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margi=
n: 16px 0;">The complaint alleges that from approximately July 2017 to arou=
nd December 2017, Gemini, directly and through others, made false or mislea=
ding statements of material facts, or omitted to state material facts, to t=
he CFTC during an evaluation of the potential self-certification of a bitco=
in futures contract by a designated contract market (DCM). The proposed bit=
coin futures contract was to be settled by reference to the spot bitcoin pr=
ice on the relevant day as determined by an auction held on Gemini=E2=80=99=
s digital asset trading platform (Gemini Bitcoin Auction).=C2=A0</p><p styl=
e=3D"margin: 16px 0;">According to the complaint, Gemini, directly and thro=
ugh the DCM, provided information to the CFTC concerning Gemini=E2=80=99s t=
rading platform and the Gemini Bitcoin Auction, and certain statements and =
information conveyed or omitted by Gemini were false or misleading with res=
pect to, among other things, facts relevant to understanding whether the pr=
oposed Bitcoin Futures Contract would be readily susceptible to manipulatio=
n.=C2=A0</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The stuff in <a href=
=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/27976693.262609/aHR0cHM6L=
y93d3cuY2Z0Yy5nb3YvbWVkaWEvNzMxNi9lbmZnZW1pbmljb21wbGFpbnQwNjAyMjIvZG93bmxv=
YWQ/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB8cb4c83f" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"=
itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none=
 !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border=
-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">the complaint</a> isn=E2=80=
=99t=C2=A0<em>that=C2=A0</em>bad. Mainly the claims are that Gemini encoura=
ged trading on its platform =E2=80=94=C2=A0by lending Bitcoins to some trad=
ers, by giving fee rebate incentives, etc. =E2=80=94=C2=A0in order to juice=
 trading activity and liquidity, but lied to the CFTC about it, so the CFTC=
 thought that all the trading was, as it were, =E2=80=9Cnatural=E2=80=9D ra=
ther than driven by incentives:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"=
>In oral and written communications to Commission staff during the Relevant=
 Period, Gemini represented that it was a =E2=80=9Cfull reserve=E2=80=9D ex=
change and that it required all transactions to be fully =E2=80=9Cpre-funde=
d.=E2=80=9D Gemini represented that the =E2=80=9Cprefunding=E2=80=9D aspect=
 of the Gemini Exchange made the Gemini Exchange and the Gemini Bitcoin Auc=
tion, and thus the Bitcoin Futures Contract, less susceptible to manipulati=
on because it increased traders=E2=80=99 cost of capital and made improper =
trading conduct more expensive to malicious actors. =E2=80=A6</p><p style=
=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Gemini did not disclose its substantial efforts to red=
uce or largely eliminate market participants=E2=80=99 cost of capital in or=
der to facilitate greater trading volume on the Gemini Exchange, including =
in the Gemini Bitcoin Auction.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Gemini=
 did not disclose to Commission staff, for example, that certain market mak=
er Gemini customers could and did obtain loans of digital assets controlled=
 by Gemini Principal-1 and Gemini Principal-2 from an entity they controlle=
d (=E2=80=9CAffiliate A=E2=80=9D) =E2=80=A6</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"=
>Gemini also did not disclose to Commission staff that before and during th=
e Relevant Period Gemini gave =E2=80=9Cadvances=E2=80=9D or =E2=80=9Ccredit=
s=E2=80=9D of fiat currency or digital assets to select customers, such tha=
t the funds could immediately be used for trading on Gemini, and that Gemin=
i provided such advances by directly crediting the customer=E2=80=99s accou=
nt.=C2=A0</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Meh? =E2=80=9CAll ou=
r trades are pre-funded=E2=80=9D and =E2=80=9Cour owners lend people money =
to pre-fund their trades=E2=80=9D are not exactly contradictory. Also there=
 was some self-trading:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Gemini =
indicated that =E2=80=9Cself-trade prevention=E2=80=9D was among the =E2=80=
=9Cattributes that promote the integrity of the auction price and discourag=
e manipulative conduct,=E2=80=9D explaining that =E2=80=9C[w]e prohibit the=
 same market participant from crossing with himself or herself (either inte=
ntionally or unintentionally) on a continuous trading order book or in a Ge=
mini Bitcoin Auction.=E2=80=9D =E2=80=A6</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In=
 fact, before in or around May 2017, Gemini did not effectively prohibit se=
lftrading in Gemini Bitcoin Auctions or have any technological means to pre=
vent self-trading from occurring in Gemini Bitcoin Auctions. =E2=80=A6=C2=
=A0For example, for one auction in December 2016, approximately 70% of the =
total auction trading volume resulted from a single auction participant tra=
ding with itself.</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">None of it i=
s like =E2=80=9CGemini=E2=80=99s Bitcoin prices were fake=E2=80=9D; it is a=
ll =E2=80=9Cwe would have been slightly less confident in Gemini=E2=80=99s =
Bitcoin prices if we had had the complete details.=E2=80=9D The message her=
e is not so much that the CFTC has lost confidence in Bitcoin futures, but =
rather that the CFTC really does not appreciate being tricked. Which is rea=
sonable.</p><table class=3D"header" width=3D"100%" border=3D"0" cellspacing=
